the GitHub command line, the GH tool. GitHub has an MCP server that has many dozens, lots,

00:13:13.219 --> 00:13:18.580
probably hundreds of tools, and if you were to take the whole GitHub MCP server, that's a lot

00:13:18.580 --> 00:13:24.020
of tools, and this matters because when you connect to an MCP server, all of the tool definitions load

00:13:24.020 --> 00:13:30.219
at the beginning, and so they're taking up part of your context window there, and that may include a

00:13:30.219 --> 00:13:36.059
lot of things that you don't need, so it's wasteful. It's wasteful for your context. It's spending

00:13:36.659 --> 00:13:43.580
tokens that you don't need, and it makes your model less efficient in terms of, you know, it can

00:13:43.580 --> 00:13:49.859
be confusing for that, and whereas the GH command utility is perfect because it's already in the

